I was hoping for something like "Room on a Broom".  The full length live action/animation movie is Spanish with English dubbing. It's awkward in my opinion and I don't usually have a problem with dubbing ("Totoro", "Ponyo", etc.). My 3 year old was mildly interested however, and I suppose that's what counts!

I would give this a half star or zero if I could. 1st off, the description should say that it is originally in Spanish and dubbed over. I think somehow a lot is lost in translation and in cultural differences. Between these two things and the length, my nearly 7y.o. niece was both confused and bored though she watched nearly to the bitter end despite the adults in the room trying to get her to switch to something better (like Room on the Broom or The Gruffalo or The Gruffalo's Child...but having just lost yet another tooth...finally even she gave up. With only 15 minutes to go!
The other issue was it was in the recommendation section alongside Room on the Broom, The Gruffalo, etc, which are all 30 minute programs whilst this was nearly 2 hours long. And the human acting seemed poor (translation/dubbing problem or truly bad acting, who's to know?) but the animation seemed ok, however much of it was mixed (humans interacting with animated creatures).
Not great dialogue for a kids movie a sort of a weird storyline.
